actions.comment:
Thanks for the detailed repro code.

Skia only implements encoders for three formats: **JPEG**, **PNG**, and **WebP**. The other values in `SKEncodedImageFormat` (BMP, GIF, ICO, HEIF, AVIF, etc.) exist because Skia can *decode* those formats, but encoding support was never added upstream. When you call `Encode()` with an unsupported format, it returns `null` rather than throwing — which then causes a `NullReferenceException` on `SaveTo()`.

As a workaround, switch to a supported format:

```csharp
SKData data = image.Encode(SKEncodedImageFormat.Png, 100);
if (data != null)
    data.SaveTo(stream);
```

This matches the findings on #320, where the maintainer confirmed the same limitation. As @nandor23 noted, this is an upstream Skia constraint rather than a SkiaSharp bug.
